 Saturday, May 22, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, May 22, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Gariahat to Park Circus. Dug up for tram track dereservation.				 																Soccer meet				 																																	Catch a match at The Telegraph Merchants Cup Football Tournament 2004, organised by CC amp;FC, on the club grounds, from 4.30 pm.				 																Screenings				 																																	Attend the screening of The Day After Tomorrow, presented by Seagrams Royal Stag and co-sponsored by The Telegraph, at Winning Streak, HHI, 10 pm. Entry by invitation. 				 																																	Dont miss the Wild Life Film Show, organised by Aranyak at Nandan II, from 2 pm to 8 pm.				 																Hard Talk				 																																	Grill Jyotirmoy Mukherjee, chairman of the Higher Secondary Council, as he interacts with readers of The Telegraph at Vidyasagar Bhavan, near Karunamoyee, in Salt Lake, at 11 am.				 																Art beat				 																																	Visit Summer Show, an all-India exhibition of paintings and sculptures, on view at CIMA Gallery from 2 pm to 7 pm.
